commit.message:
Add license classifier to setup.py

To have unified license specification like in https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid/blob/master/setup.py#L85

Note that will allow (imperfect) tools like https://github.com/pivotal/LicenseFinder to automatically recognize the license, which is currently (v6.6.1) recognized as unknown.

commit.message:
Fix python 3.3 path in travis.yml

Due to python 3.3 not available anymore in default travis ubuntu version (now 16.04, xenial), python 3.3 is taken from 14.04 (trusty) instead.
Fix taken from https://github.com/travis-ci/travis-ci/issues/9133#issuecomment-531022359
